Description: Privacy-first, local-first voice assistant for Linux
 MimOSA (Mimicking OS Assistant) is a voice-controlled AI assistant that lives
 in your operating system: it controls apps, finds files, manages system
 settings, and conducts research through natural conversation.
 .
 MimOSA keeps private conversations on your machine, learns your preferences
 over time, sends no telemetry, and can run its language model fully locally.
 .
 This package installs MimOSA into a self-contained virtual environment under
 /opt/mimosa and provides the "mimosa" command. The on-device voice models
 (Whisper, Piper) are downloaded on first use.
